1
00:00:00,031 --> 00:00:02,613
SPEAKER_00: Disasters rarely begin at the moment of impact.

2
00:00:03,355 --> 00:00:08,742
SPEAKER_00: They begin when a system gets used to explaining away what it should have stopped to understand.

3
00:00:10,044 --> 00:00:15,551
SPEAKER_00: Challenger was a long sequence of accommodations, each one easier to defend than the whole chain would have been.

4
00:00:16,532 --> 00:00:22,679
SPEAKER_00: The smoke at T plus 0.678 seconds is why the story should not start with the explosion.

5
00:00:22,660 --> 00:00:24,801
SPEAKER_00: The first visible warning was small.

6
00:00:25,643 --> 00:00:26,364
SPEAKER_00: Then it vanished.

7
00:00:27,265 --> 00:00:29,547
SPEAKER_00: For a while, everything looked normal.

8
00:00:30,408 --> 00:00:32,771
SPEAKER_00: The same thing had already happened inside the organization.

9
00:00:33,731 --> 00:00:34,673
SPEAKER_00: A warning appeared.

10
00:00:35,213 --> 00:00:36,393
SPEAKER_00: The system explained it.

11
00:00:36,975 --> 00:00:38,076
SPEAKER_00: The launch continued.

12
00:00:39,057 --> 00:00:41,740
SPEAKER_00: That is why the next case belongs beside Challenger.

13
00:00:42,420 --> 00:00:44,883
SPEAKER_00: THERAK25 is not another space story.

14
00:00:45,584 --> 00:00:50,389
SPEAKER_00: It is a smaller room, a medical machine, a software interface,

15
00:00:50,368 --> 00:00:54,240
SPEAKER_00: and operators trying to explain errors the machine was not built to make visible.

16
00:00:54,942 --> 00:00:55,784
SPEAKER_00: The form changes.

17
00:00:56,527 --> 00:00:57,509
SPEAKER_00: The pattern does not.

18
00:00:58,231 --> 00:01:00,639
SPEAKER_00: Confidence moves faster than verification.

19
00:01:01,722 --> 00:01:02,243
SPEAKER_00: Next time.

20
00:01:02,886 --> 00:01:03,588
SPEAKER_00: Therac 25.

21
00:01:04,631 --> 00:01:10,909
SPEAKER_00: A medical machine that exposed what happens when software confidence outruns the evidence users can see.
